00:15:05.650 --> 00:15:06.460 align:middle line:90%
Here, let me get a gun.

00:15:06.460 --> 00:15:08.335 align:middle line:84%
We'll shoot you and see
if you die, you know?

00:15:08.335 --> 00:15:09.790 align:middle line:90%
I mean, we can't do that.

00:15:09.790 --> 00:15:14.050 align:middle line:90%
So they want to know like I do.

00:15:14.050 --> 00:15:16.600 align:middle line:90%
I was lucky to be killed.

00:15:16.600 --> 00:15:17.950 align:middle line:90%
Think about what I'm saying.

00:15:17.950 --> 00:15:20.440 align:middle line:84%
I was lucky to be
killed and then

00:15:20.440 --> 00:15:22.870 align:middle line:84%
to come back so that I
could say all of this

00:15:22.870 --> 00:15:23.980 align:middle line:90%
and know all of this.

00:15:23.980 --> 00:15:27.300 align:middle line:90%


00:15:27.300 --> 00:15:29.430 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, my sense about
near-death experience is

00:15:29.430 --> 00:15:32.940 align:middle line:84%
the same as when I hear a
story about psychic experience

00:15:32.940 --> 00:15:36.570 align:middle line:84%
or mystical experience, or in
fact, any strange experience.

00:15:36.570 --> 00:15:40.320 align:middle line:84%
On the one hand, it is
somebody's actual experience,

00:15:40.320 --> 00:15:43.740 align:middle line:84%
so you need to listen to
it carefully and compare it

00:15:43.740 --> 00:15:46.710 align:middle line:84%
against other
people's experiences.

00:15:46.710 --> 00:15:49.170 align:middle line:84%
Then the question is
if it's very strange,

00:15:49.170 --> 00:15:50.700 align:middle line:84%
if it doesn't happen
very often, you

00:15:50.700 --> 00:15:54.400 align:middle line:84%
have to figure out how to
interpret what it means.

00:15:54.400 --> 00:15:56.710 align:middle line:84%
Some people will interpret
a near-death experience

00:15:56.710 --> 00:15:58.690 align:middle line:84%
as meaning that
they have literally

00:15:58.690 --> 00:16:00.700 align:middle line:84%
separated from their
body in some way

00:16:00.700 --> 00:16:04.000 align:middle line:84%
and the identification
of who they are

00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:06.130 align:middle line:90%
is no longer like this.

00:16:06.130 --> 00:16:07.020 align:middle line:90%
It's something else.

00:16:07.020 --> 00:16:09.710 align:middle line:84%
A spirit, a soul,
something like that.

00:16:09.710 --> 00:16:12.160 align:middle line:84%
It's been very difficult
to do scientific research

00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:15.490 align:middle line:84%
on these kinds of
experiences because it's not

00:16:15.490 --> 00:16:19.720 align:middle line:84%
ethical to try to induce
a near-death experience.

00:16:19.720 --> 00:16:21.560 align:middle line:84%
And they tend to
happen spontaneously,

00:16:21.560 --> 00:16:24.620 align:middle line:84%
so it's very difficult to know
when it's going to happen.

00:16:24.620 --> 00:16:28.810 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand, there are
instances in which people claim

00:16:28.810 --> 00:16:31.420 align:middle line:84%
to separate from their
body and they can correctly

00:16:31.420 --> 00:16:35.410 align:middle line:84%
describe things from other
positions, other places.

00:16:35.410 --> 00:16:37.540 align:middle line:84%
That's when I become more
interested, because those

00:16:37.540 --> 00:16:40.110 align:middle line:90%
are things that can be tested.

00:16:40.110 --> 00:16:41.670 align:middle line:84%
And you don't need
to have somebody

00:16:41.670 --> 00:16:45.280 align:middle line:84%
in a near-death condition
in order to test it.

00:16:45.280 --> 00:16:48.450 align:middle line:84%
So what we have focused on,
what my research focuses on

00:16:48.450 --> 00:16:51.870 align:middle line:84%
mostly is people who
are not near death,

00:16:51.870 --> 00:16:54.300 align:middle line:84%
but just completely
ordinary states

00:16:54.300 --> 00:16:57.270 align:middle line:84%
who are asked, for example,
to describe something

00:16:57.270 --> 00:17:00.180 align:middle line:90%
at a distance or that is hidden.

00:17:00.180 --> 00:17:03.410 align:middle line:84%
And we have pretty good evidence
that people can do that.

00:17:03.410 --> 00:17:08.810 align:middle line:10%
>> For me to share with you that
I have perfect memory of every

00:17:08.810 --> 00:17:11.569 align:middle line:10%
